# C++ Test Conventions

When editing or creating test files in `native/tests/`:

## Naming
- File name: `test_<module>.cpp` (mirrors the source file name)
- Test tags: `[module_name]` (e.g., `[risk_calculator]`)

## Framework
- Catch2 v3: `#include <catch2/catch_test_macros.hpp>`
- Use `TEST_CASE` with descriptive names and `SECTION` for sub-scenarios
- For floating-point: `#include <catch2/matchers/catch_matchers_floating_point.hpp>`

## What to Test
- All public API functions from the corresponding header
- Edge cases: zero, negative, boundary values
- Trading-specific: invalid strikes, expired contracts, zero notional, European vs American exercise
- Error paths: invalid inputs, empty states
- Numerical precision: use `Catch::Matchers::WithinAbs` or `WithinRel`

## What to Avoid
- Tests requiring network or TWS connection (use mocks)
- Hardcoded absolute paths
- Trivial constructor-only tests with no logic

## Registration
- New test files must be added to `native/tests/CMakeLists.txt`
- Run: `ctest --test-dir build -R test_<module> --output-on-failure`
